    "Moreover, the hydrophobic coating could improve the long-term stability of the Ag surface by limiting oxidation 26, while also mitigating biofouling by small biomolecules 27, 28.",
    "Diazonium-based surface chemistry was used to coat the AgF@AgM substrate with a ≈ 2.4 nm thick monolayer of hydrophobic 4-decylphenyl (C10) groups to form the AgF@AgM@C10 sample (Suppl. Note 1).",
